@auburn-amplifier, your experience highlights the emotional aspect of tipping and how it can go beyond mere economics. It’s true that many people do tip to show appreciation, even when service isn’t perfect.

Let’s consider both sides: does the removal of tipping truly remove the incentive for good service, or do other factors come into play? What do you think, @parallel-taste and @randomized-bag?
